name: Chandler Center for the Arts
directions: Back entrance by parking lot. To access with a wheelchair, go down the hall to the right and it is right on the corner, only ~10 ft. from the entrance. Once in the lower level, two gendered single stalls are to the right about 20 feet away. Others can take the stairs right in front of the entrance and the restrooms are directly right at the bottom of the stairs.
comment: Is only a good option for Chandler High Students. The door is locked at 2:15 Mon-Fri and usually closed on weekend. Most foot traffic is during third period, as dance's changing rooms are down there. All other times have very few people. A great resource for Chandler High Students.
